  "notes": [
    "Transfer Admission Screening Policy Transfer students must complete the following courses, or their articulated equivalents, with a combined minimum GPA of 2.8 or better by the end of the spring term prior to transferring in the fall: MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics CSE 16: Applied Discrete Mathematics CSE 30: Programming Abstractions: Python One of the following courses: ECE 13: Computer Systems and C Programming CSE 13S: Computer Systems and C Programming CSE 12: Computer Systems and Assembly Language and Lab ADDITIONAL TRANSFER INFORMATION Transfer students applying for the fall term are strongly recommended to have completed at least three of the five required courses by the end of the fall term prior to transfer, with an overall GPA of 2.8 or higher in the three courses. In addition, completing all but one of the following courses prior to transfer is strongly recommended to ensure timely graduation: CSE 20: Beginning Programming in Python CSE 12: Computer Systems and Assembly Language and Lab AM 10: Mathematical Methods for Engineers I OR MATH 21: Linear Algebra ECE 13: Computer Systems and C Programming OR CSE 13S: Computer Systems and C Programming Prospective students are also encouraged to complete the Intersegmental General Education Transfer Curriculum (IGETC) or to complete all UCSC general education requirements before matriculation. Please visit the Baskin Engineering Undergraduate Experience website to learn more about this major.",
    "All transfer applicants must satisfy University of California admissions eligibility requirements and campus admission selection criteria. All admission requirements must be completed by the end of spring prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility requirements and admission to UC Santa Cruz, please visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that ensures your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require the completion of specific preparatory courses and/or minimum GPA requirements. For detailed information about the screening requirements for this major, please refer to \"Transfer Admission Screening Policy\" below. Additional preparatory coursework listed in the \u201cRecommended Preparation\u201d section are not required for admission, but are strongly recommended. Completion of these courses will help ensure timely progress toward degree completion. More information and a list of screening majors and non-screening majors may be found on the Admissions website.",
    "The UC Santa Cruz Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate (IB), and A-Level examination credit policies may be found in the UC Santa Cruz General Catalog . AP, IBH, and A-level exams may or may not satisfy course requirements, depending on the specific exam."
